A 45-year-old suspect is due to appear at the George Magistrate Court in Western Cape on Wednesday for alleged drug dealing.The suspect was arrested on Christmas day along N9 between Uniondale and Harold by the Directorate for Priority crime investigation together with local police and K9 unit along the N9 between Uniondale and Harold.Hawks spokesman Captain Lloyd Ramovha said, &#8221; The George bound suspect, reportedly from Soweto in Gauteng was swiftly intercepted after information came to light that he was enroute allegedly transporting drugs.&#8220;The search was with the help of a K9 narcotics dog uncovered a false compartment containing about 75000 units of Mandrax tablets valued at approximately R3.8 million.&#8221;Ramovha added that Just over R11 000 in cash was also seized.The suspect is facing charges relating to drug dealing.Meanwhile, In November the Western Cape police arrested four suspects for drug dealing near a smallholding in Vredenburg.The four accused were found in possession of drugs worth more than R7 million.The suspects are due to appear on the 13th of January 2017 in the Vredenburg Magistrate Court.Ramovha said, &#8220;It is within our mission and competence to continue unravelling high-level criminal enterprises by focusing on disrupting the business side of the criminal system.&#8220;Criminals, Be warned! We have our thumb on the pulse.&#8221;TNA Reporter